### Describe the bug

I'm trying to set up a site with multiple Server SPA's.  Each maps to a sub-path on the web root e.g. "https://localhost/red" and  "https://localhost/blue".  To map "fix" sub-path I set the following in `Program`.

```
app.UseWhen(ctx => ctx.Request.Path.StartsWithSegments("/blue"), appBlue =>
{
    appBlue.UsePathBase("/blue");
});

app.UseWhen(ctx => ctx.Request.Path.StartsWithSegments("/red"), appRed =>
{
    appRed.UsePathBase("/red");
});

app.MapBlazorHub();

app.MapFallbackToPage("/blue/{*path:nonfile}", "/Blue");
app.MapFallbackToPage("/red/{*path:nonfile}", "/Red");
app.MapFallbackToPage("/_Host");

app.Run();
```

I don't set the path in `<base href="/" />` on the SPA startup file.


### Expected Behavior

It all works except the Blazor UI events, such a button clicks.  My initial thought was that the SPA wasn't linked up to the Hub Session, but that's not the case.  Routing works, and if you put a breakpoint on `OnInitializedAsync` in `FetchData` it gets hit.  However, `IncrementCount` in `Counter` never gets hit.

I would expect either or neither to work, definitely not what I'm seeing!


### Steps To Reproduce

Create a solution based on the Blazor Server template.

Update `Program`

```csharp
app.UseStaticFiles();

app.UseRouting();
// Set the PathBase
app.UsePathBase("/blue");

app.MapBlazorHub();
app.MapFallbackToPage("/_Host");

app.Run();
```

Update `_Layout.cshtml` to set the css and js paths:

```html
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <base href="~/" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/bootstrap/bootstrap.min.css" />
    <link href="/css/site.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link href="/Blazr.EndPoint.styles.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <component type="typeof(HeadOutlet)" render-mode="ServerPrerendered" />
</head>
//....
    <script src="_framework/blazor.server.js"></script>
//.....
```

Add breakpoint:

1. Line 46 in `FetchData`:

```csharp
 forecasts = await ForecastService.GetForecastAsync(DateTime.Now);
```

2. Line 16 in Counter:

```csharp
 currentCount++;
```

Run the application.

Both should be hit in the root https://localhost/counter.

Now navigate to https://localhost:7104/blue.  The first breakpoint gets hit, but not the second.

